Maintainer: Sven Kotlarski <sven.kotlarski@meteoswiss.ch>
Description: An implementation of quantile mapping (QM) based on empirical quantiles and developed at ETH Zurich and MeteoSwiss.
    The package is used for bias-correcting and downscaling EURO-CORDEX RCM output within the frame of the CH2018 Swiss Climate
    Change Scenarios. Several meteorological variables can be handled. New extremes are corrected according
    to the correction function for the highes/lowest empirical quantile considered. This implementation is
    based on and extends the code of Rajczak et al., International Journal of Climatology, 2016. Function families:
    cal... -> Calendar conversion functions. helper... -> Helper functions. meta... -> Functions to handle climate
    model meta data. qm... -> Quantile-mapping functions. selbox... -> Functions handling the appropriate selection
    of climate model grid cells. timstats... -> Functions for temporal statistics.
Imports:
    ncdf4
